HEADWORD: Hydrangea
<hw>Hy*dran"ge*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>peop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"y`dwr</grk> water + <?/ vessel, capsule: cf. F.
<ets>hydrang⟦eacute⟧e</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
shrubby plants bearing opposite leaves and large heads of showy flowers,
white, or of various colors. <spn>Hydrangea hortensis</spn>, the common
garden species, is a native of China or Japan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

